      "raw_text": "(ScrippS News Association\n\n\nSEATTLE, March 1.-The Hill\nHartman contest has been renew\ned on the Olympic peninsula with\nthe Union Pacific and Milwaukee\nlined up against the Hill interests\nRockefeller money is behind Har\nriman. The prize is the immense\ntimber resources of the peninsula\nSurveyors for the Northern Pacific\nand for the Hartman combine are\nat work all over the peninsula run\nming parallel lines in a race tc\ngirdle the territory with tracks\n\n\nThe Milwaukee has already pur\nchased immense tracts of timber\nhere. 1t Is now positive that the\nUnion Pacific and Milwaukee will\nuse a joint track from Seattle tC\nPortland."
